      "full_name": "PMC Tsarskie Volki",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "PMC Tsarskie Volki is a Russian private military company that directly participates in Russian combat operations in Ukraine. Combatants of PMC Tsarskie Volki actively participate in Russian operations in the so-called “Donetsk People’s Republic” and the so-called “Luhansk People’s Republic”. The organisation predominantly consists of military-technical experts who work on the development of weapons and explosive materials on behalf of the Russian Armed Forces. PMC Tsarskie Volki has provided military-technical assistance to units of the so-called “Donetsk People’s Republic” and “Luhansk People’s Republic” and has trained them in reconnaissance and assault activities. Furthermore, PMC Tsarskie Volki has designed and tested hundreds of weapons and explosives within the context of Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine. For example, PMC Tsarskie Volki has developed the so-called “Marker” robotic tank which has served to destroy Ukrainian armoured vehicles.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}